{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/how-to-opt-out-of-dark-mode-on-iOS","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>If you are not using Xcode 11 or later (i,e iOS 13 or later SDK), your app has not automatically opted to support dark mode. So, there’s no need to opt out of dark mode.<br>\nIf you are using Xcode 11 or later, the system has automatically enabled dark mode for your app.<br>\nThere are two approaches to disable dark mode depending on your preference. You can disable it entirely or disable it for any specific window, view, or view controller.</p>\n<h4 id=\"disable-dark-mode-entirely-for-your-app\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#disable-dark-mode-entirely-for-your-app\" aria-label=\"disable dark mode entirely for your app permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Disable Dark Mode Entirely for your App</h4>\n<p>You can disable dark mode by including the <code class=\"language-text\">UIUserInterfaceStyle</code> key with a value as <code class=\"language-text\">Light</code> in your app’s Info.plist file.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 700px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/blog-website/static/d49e829ea4b004735e69ae76b7f07e41/3204e/info-plist.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 2.2857142857142856%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg%20xmlns=\\'http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\\'%20width=\\'400\\'%20height=\\'9\\'%20viewBox=\\'0%200%20400%209\\'%20preserveAspectRatio=\\'none\\'%3e%3cpath%20d=\\'M0%205v4h401V0H0v5\\'%20fill=\\'%2370C80F\\'%20fill-rule=\\'evenodd\\'/%3e%3c/svg%3e'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Top iOS Development Resources To Follow\"\n        title=\"Top iOS Development Resources To Follow\"\n        src=\"/blog-website/static/d49e829ea4b004735e69ae76b7f07e41/39600/info-plist.png\"\n        srcset=\"/blog-website/static/d49e829ea4b004735e69ae76b7f07e41/1aaec/info-plist.png 175w,\n/blog-website/static/d49e829ea4b004735e69ae76b7f07e41/98287/info-plist.png 350w,\n/blog-website/static/d49e829ea4b004735e69ae76b7f07e41/39600/info-plist.png 700w,\n/blog-website/static/d49e829ea4b004735e69ae76b7f07e41/3204e/info-plist.png 802w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>This ignores the user’s preference and always applies a light appearance to your app.</p>\n<h4 id=\"disable-dark-mode-for-window-view-or-view-controller\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#disable-dark-mode-for-window-view-or-view-controller\" aria-label=\"disable dark mode for window view or view controller permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Disable dark mode for Window, View, or View Controller</h4>\n<p>You can force your interface to always appear in a light or dark style by setting the <code class=\"language-text\">overrideUserInterfaceStyle</code> property of the appropriate window, view, or view controller.</p>\n<h6 id=\"view-controllers\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#view-controllers\" aria-label=\"view controllers permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>View controllers:</h6>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"swift\"><pre class=\"language-swift\"><code class=\"language-swift\"><span class=\"token keyword\">override</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">func</span> <span class=\"token function\">viewDidLoad</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">super</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">viewDidLoad</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">/* view controller’s views and child view controllers\n     always adopt a light interface style. */</span>\n    overrideUserInterfaceStyle <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>light\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<h6 id=\"views\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#views\" aria-label=\"views permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Views:</h6>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"swift\"><pre class=\"language-swift\"><code class=\"language-swift\"><span class=\"token comment\">// The view and all of its subviews always adopt light style.</span>\nyouView<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>overrideUserInterfaceStyle <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>light</code></pre></div>\n<h6 id=\"window\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#window\" aria-label=\"window permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Window:</h6>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"swift\"><pre class=\"language-swift\"><code class=\"language-swift\"><span class=\"token comment\">/* Everything in the window adopts the style,\n including the root view controller and all presentation controllers that\n display content in that window.*/</span>\nwindow<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>overrideUserInterfaceStyle <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>light</code></pre></div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Note: Apple strongly encourages to support dark mode in your app. So,\nyou can only disable dark mode temporarily.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Read more from Apple’s documentation here: <a href=\"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/appkit/supporting_dark_mode_in_your_interface/choosing_a_specific_interface_style_for_your_ios_app\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Choosing a Specific Interface Style for Your iOS App</a>\n<br/><br/>\nThis post was originally written to answer a Stackoverflow <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/58062075/1835803\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">question</a>.</p>","timeToRead":2,"frontmatter":{"title":"How to opt-out of dark mode on iOS","date":"September 23, 2019","excerpt":"Here's how you can opt-out of Apple's new dark interface style on iOS. You can either opt-out of dark mode entirely or choose specific views, view controllers, or window.","tag":"iOS Development","path":"/how-to-opt-out-of-dark-mode-on-iOS"}}},"pageContext":{"pagePath":"/how-to-opt-out-of-dark-mode-on-iOS","previous":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Cocoapods: Find the dependencies of a Pod","path":"/find-the-dependencies-of-a-pod"}},"next":{"frontmatter":{"title":"iOS design guide","path":"/iOS-design-guide"}}}}}